modules.description: This module implements a PPX rewriter for generating JavaScript interoperability code from OCaml type declarations and module expressions. It provides functions to transform OCaml types into JavaScript conversion functions, rewrite module structures with JS bindings, and handle attributes used in JS interop. Concrete use cases include automatically deriving `js_of` and `js_to` functions for types and generating JS-compatible module exports.

This module defines configuration flags for attribute and location checking during JavaScript API generation. It works with boolean values to control validation behavior in the PPX processing pipeline. Concrete use cases include enabling stricter checks for attributes or source locations when generating OCaml bindings for JavaScript code.
